<chapter id="installing" xreflabel="Installing">
<title>Installing pdb2pqr</title>

&source_roll-installing-standard;

<section id="installing-running-server" xreflabel="On an existing server">
<title>Adding Roll to the existing server</title>
<para>
The pdb2pqr Roll can be added to an existing server (or frontend). 
Assume that you have an ISO image of the roll called pdb2pqr.iso. 
The following procedure will install the Roll:
<screen>
# rocks add roll pdb2pqr.iso
# rocks enable roll pdb2pqr
# cd /export/rocks/install
# rocks create distro
# rocks run roll pdb2pqr | /bin/sh
</screen>
</para>
</section>

<section id="installing-nodes" xreflabel="Adding the Roll to Nodes">
<title>Adding the Roll to Nodes</title>

<para>
To add the the Service Pack Roll to the nodes of your cluster, you'll
need to reinstall the nodes.
</para>

<para>
To reinstall all your nodes, as root execute:
</para>

<para>
<screen>
# rocks set host compute boot action=install
# rocks run host compute command=reboot
</screen>
</para>

</section>

</chapter>
